{
  "texts": [
    "While not consistently doing so, Llama-2 has the greatest incidence of positive pushback to potentially harmful completions (§4.6), thereby positioning itself as taking an active approach to addressing stereotyping harms.",
    "As mentioned above, Mistral also produced notable examples.",
    "It is also a direction in search engine autocompletion, where certain engines (as Google) introduce positive valence into results for sensitive queries, rather than blocking them entirely (Duck-DuckGo) or letting the results flow with less moderation (Yahoo!)",
    "As they make themselves available for integration into search engines, LLMs are at the cusp of such decision-making and making public their positioning.",
    "It should be noted here that we also find supporting evidence of toxic degeneration in longer outputs (Ganguli et al. 2022; Röttger et al. 2024)."
  ]
}